{"section": "2.11.2: Extended Euclidean Algorithm.", "qid": 3, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  The image below shows the sequence of numbers generated by Euclid's algorithm on inputs\n225 and 60 as well as partial results for the extended algorithm.\n </p>\n <img alt=\"Sequence of numbers is as follows: 225, 60, 45, 15. The third term, 45, is determined by the expression 225-(B*60). The fourth term, 15, is determined by the expression 60-(A*45).\" class=\"zyimage centered-image\" height=\"undefined\" src=\"https://zytools.zybooks.com/zyAuthor/WGU_C960_DiscreteMath2/6/IMAGES/embedded_image_1_57cfdd14-c592-c393-7173-38d2fcc9de97_gynA7xf9oIXvzwTthKad.png\" title=\"\" width=\"undefined\"/>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   4)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   The two linear equations above can be used to express gcd(225, 60) as a linear combination of 225 and 60:\n   <br/>\n   <span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n    15 = C \u00b7 225 + D \u00b7 60\n   </span>\n   <br/>\n   <br/>\n   What is the correct value for D?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <div class=\"question-container flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"input\">\n   <pre><!----><textarea class=\"zb-text-area hide-scrollbar ember-text-area ember-view\" cols=\"20\" id=\"ember108\" rows=\"1\" spellcheck=\"false\"></textarea><!----></pre>\n   <div class=\"buttons flex-row\">\n    <button class=\"check-button zb-button primary raised ember-view\" id=\"ember109\">\n     <!-- -->\n     <span class=\"title\">\n      Check\n     </span>\n    </button>\n    <button class=\"show-answer-button zb-button secondary ember-view\" id=\"ember110\" style=\"\">\n     <!-- -->\n     <span class=\"title\">\n      Show answer\n     </span>\n    </button>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </div>\n</div>\n", "choices": [], "answer": "4", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation forfeit\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Answer\n </p>\n <div class=\"answers\">\n  <!-- -->\n  <span class=\"forfeit-answer\">\n   4\n  </span>\n </div>\n 15 = 60 - 45\n <br/>\n 45 = 225 - (3 \u00b7 60)\n <br/>\n <br/>\n The second equation replaces 45 in the first equation with  a linear combination of 225 and 60.\n <br/>\n <br/>\n 15 = 60 - (225 - 3\u00b760) = 4\u00b760 - 225.\n <br/>\n The coefficient of 60 is 4.\n</div>\n"}